# NOAA Deep Sea Corals
- This dataset contains information about deep sea corals
and sponges collected by NOAA and NOAA's partners. It is tailored to the
occurrences of azooxanthellates - a subset of all corals and all sponge species
(i.e. they don't have symbiotic relationships with certain microbes).
- Contains
geolocations of deep sea corals and sponges
- Records only consists of
observations deeper than 50 meters to truly focus on the **deep sea** corals and
sponges.

Link to dataset: https://www.kaggle.com/noaa/deep-sea-
corals/downloads/deep-sea-corals.zip/1

-
Changing to 0 might not be the best option -- come back to this later if
necessary
- Also, these are observations were >= 50m, so add 50 to each value

```{.python .input  n=14}
def manip_loc_acc(measurement):
    '''
    measurement : str or float
    
    Purpose is to manipulate values in LocationAccuracy column to allow LocationAccuracy.dtype == float64
    
    Returns None or float
    '''
    measurement = str(measurement)
    if 'nan' in measurement:
        return None
    # Convert values > 1000m to 1001m -- may need to change this value
    elif '>' in measurement:
        measurement = '1001m'
    # Removes m
    measurement = measurement[:-1]
    return float(measurement)

df['LocationAccuracy'] = df['LocationAccuracy'].map(manip_loc_acc)
```

- cf. = 'confer' or 'compare to'
- Decided to remove cf. when it is at the
beginning and have it represent the genus, even though it doesn't - close enough

```{.python .input  n=25}
def manip_sciname(sciname):
    '''
    sciname : str
    
    Removes sp
    Removes cf. in the middle - e.g., Paracyathus cf. fulvus => Paracyathus is true genus
    Removes cf. in beginning - e.g., cf. Penares sp. => Penares is a comparable genus
    Removes nr. (near)
    Removes (n. subgenus)
    
    Returns str
    '''
    if 'cf.' in sciname:
        test = sciname.split()
        # Only two rows with Genus == 'cf.' and both are Kulamanamana
        if sciname == 'cf.':
            return 'Kulamanamana'
        # 'cf.' is in the middle, test[0] == true genus
        elif test[1] == 'cf.':
            return test[0]
        # 'cf.' in beginning, test[1] == comparable genus, but not true genus... good enough for purpose of this project
        else:
            return test[1]
    elif ' sp' in sciname:
        return sciname.split()[0]
    elif ' nr.' in sciname:
        return sciname.split()[0]
    else:
        return sciname

df['Genus'] = df['Genus'].map(manip_sciname)
```

## Latitude, Longitude
- Two features representing a 3-dimensional space
- Map
to x, y, z coordinates

```{.python .input  n=36}
# Convert degrees to radians
lat = np.radians(df['latitude'])
lon = np.radians(df['longitude'])

R = 6371000. # Approximate Earth radius in m
df['x'] = R * np.cos(lat) * np.cos(lon)
df['y'] = R * np.cos(lat) * np.sin(lon)
df['z'] = R * np.sin(lat)
```
